rows.Rate Schedule:
BEV-1   

The BEV-1 rate option is applicable to customers with kW usage at or below 100 kW. Customers may be on the BEV-1 or BEV-2 at usage of 100 kW based on the customer's preference.  BEV-1 is for Secondary Voltage service.

BEV-2-S   Secondary

The BEV-2 rate option is applicable to customers with kW usage at or above 100 kW. Customers may be on the BEV-1 or BEV-2 at usage of 100 kW based on the customer's preference.  BEV-2 is designed with a Primary and Secondary Voltage service option.

BEV-2-P   Primary/Transmission

The BEV-2 rate option is applicable to customers with kW usage at or above 100 kW. Customers may be on the BEV-1 or BEV-2 at usage of 100 kW based on the customer's preference.  BEV-2 is designed with a Primary and Secondary Voltage service option.  Transmission Voltage customers are eligible for enrollment on the BEV-2 Primary rate.
1/ $/kW for informational purposes only.  This does not constitute an additional charge. See tariff for further details.

rows.Rate Schedule: 1/Effective January 1, 2006, agricultural "ratcheted" demand charges, demand charge limiters, minimum demands, drought relief options, and balance of contract were
eliminated.  Demands will be measured each month, with demand charges based only upon the demand in the current month, rather than "ratcheted" or "seasonal
billing" demands which considered demands in all months of the same season in the past year, or minimum demands based on the two largest motors.
2/Effective May 1, 2006, the voluntary TOU one time reprogramming charge of $85 if there is a TOU meter already present, and one time $441 meter installation charge if there is no TOU
meter, were eliminated.  The lower daily TOU meter charge continues to apply to customers who were on Rate E or F as of May 1, 2006.  Rate B or C applies to all other customers.
3/Based on estimated forecast. Average bundled rates provided only for general reference, and individual customer's average rate will depend on its applicable kw, kWh and TOU data.
